Defendant in custody.   
Count 4 - Felony Bail Jumping - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1-3 and 5-7.   Motion granted.   Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years to commence upon completion of prison sentences on 15 CF 755 and 15 CF 612.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Reimburse Metro Drug Unit $140.00 for buy money; 
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
5) Use only one doctor that prescribes her medication and only one pharmacist;
6) Have no contact with Jason Temple unless approved by agent;
7) Obtain GED/HSED;
8) Maintain full-time employment/schooling/work search combination; 
9) Pay costs of action; 
10) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
11) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.  
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.   
